SUMMARY:DeKorte Park Waterfowl Walk
DESCRIPTION:Grab your binoculars and join the NJ Audubon for a waterfowl walk along the wetlands of DeKorte Park in Lyndhurst!  Bring your binoculars and your observation skills as we walk the boardwalks of Richard W. DeKorte Park searching for winter ducks\, raptors\, and more during this 2.5 hour walk. Open to birders of all expertise levels and ages. Families\, teens\, and adults welcome. \nThis program takes place entirely outside\, please dress appropriately. Extra binoculars will be available to borrow. \nPRE-REGISTRATION REQUIRED \nCOST: FREE \nCANCELLATION: NJ Audubon’s programs require a minimum number of registrants to run. If we cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, all participants will be notified as soon as possible and are eligible for a full refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 48 hours in advance. Sorry\, no refund for cancellations less than 48 hours in advance unless due to health emergencies; however registrations can be transferred to another program in the future. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/dekorte-park-waterfowl-walk/
LOCATION:Richard W. DeKorte Park\, 1 DeKorte Park\, Lyndhurst\, NJ\, 07071\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bird Walk,Birding,Family Program,Lorrimer Sanctuary
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://njaudubon.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/DeKorte-Park-Waterfowl-Walk-03.2026.jpeg
GEO:40.7864699;-74.1023301
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Richard W. DeKorte Park 1 DeKorte Park Lyndhurst NJ 07071 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=1 DeKorte Park:geo:-74.1023301,40.7864699
END:VEVENT
