UID:10010664-1773943200-1773946800@njaudubon.org
SUMMARY:Native Gardening: Creating a Spring Checklist
DESCRIPTION:Join NCCM staff and naturalists as we partner with the Cape May County Library System for special lectures and workshops!  \nNative gardening can seem overwhelming\, but it isn’t too late to get started this Spring. Shake off that winter frost and get ready for a season of connecting with your garden. Join the Nature Center of Cape May staff to walk through all the items to add to your spring gardening to-do list. We will cover everything from planning your garden to prepping the space! Plus\, we will add in our favorite native gardening tips and tricks. Pre-registration requested. \n\n\nCOST: FREE \n\n\nWHEN: Thursday\, March 19th 6:00-7:00pm \nWHERE: Stone Harbor Library (9516 2nd Avenue\, Stone Harbor\, NJ 08247)\, Events Room \n\n\nCANCELLATION: NJ Audubon’s CMBO programs are virtually never cancelled. If we cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, all participants will be notified as soon as possible and are eligible for a full refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 48 hours in advance. Sorry\, no refund for cancellations less than 48 hours in advance unless due to health emergencies; however\, registrations can be transferred to another program in the future. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/native-gardening-creating-a-spring-checklist/
LOCATION:Stone Harbor Library – Events Room\, 9516 2nd Avenue\, Stone Harbor\, NJ\, 08247\, United States
CATEGORIES:Lecture,Nature Center of Cape May,Workshop
END:VEVENT
