SUMMARY:Constellations and Cocoa
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy the natural beauty of the stars at night\, learn about the seasonal constellations\, and warm up with a cup of hot cocoa! Join us for this after-dark program all about the stars! We’ll be looking up as we learn all about the constellations and their myths as we sip on hot cocoa during this family-friendly program. Binoculars and telescope for viewing will be provided. \nThe first part of this event will take place indoors\, then we will head outside to observe the stars. Please dress appropriately. This event is weather dependent and will be cancelled if there is rain or cloud cover\, participants will be notified of cancellations by 6:00 PM. \nCOST: $8 members / $10 nonmembers \nCANCELLATION: NJ Audubon’s programs require a minimum number of registrants to run. If we cancel\, due to lack of participation\, severe weather\, or unforeseen circumstances\, all participants will be notified as soon as possible and are eligible for a full refund. Participants may cancel without penalty if greater than 48 hours in advance. Sorry\, no refund for cancellations less than 48 hours in advance unless due to health emergencies; however\, registrations can be transferred to another program in the future. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://njaudubon.org/event/constellations-and-cocoa-6/
LOCATION:Lorrimer Sanctuary\, 790 Ewing Avenue\, Franklin Lakes\, NJ\, 07417\, United States
CATEGORIES:Family Program,Lorrimer Sanctuary
